  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Peel and chop the shallots, and caramelize them in a pan over medium heat for 5 minutes.",
    "Shred the cabbage and mix with the cumin, coriander, nutmeg, and a pinch of salt and pepper.",
    "In a separate pan, toast the cloves of garlic and ginger until fragrant, then mince them.",
    "Mix the shredded cabbage with the toasted garlic and ginger, and add in the coconut milk and chicken broth.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and top with the caramelized shallots.",
    "Roast in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the cabbage is tender.",
    "Let the dish rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro if desired."
  ],
